# User Flows

Greek learning app with SRS-based vocabulary practice and timed production drills.

## Quick Reference

```
/                    Dashboard (home)
/login               Sign in (password or passkey)
/register            Create account
/try                 Anonymous drill (conversion flow)
/practice            Redirects to /practice/speed
/practice/speed      Timed mixed drills (with ?focus= filters)
/practice/memory     Memory drill hub (articles, pronouns, possessives, contractions)
/practice/memory/*   Individual memory drills (timed paradigm recall)
/practice/:tab       SRS drills (vocabulary, review)
/learn               Learn landing page (section cards)
/learn/conversations Themed dialogues
/learn/phrases       Common expressions
/learn/nouns         Noun browser by gender/category
/learn/verbs         Verb browser by conjugation family
/learn/verbs/:verbId Full verb conjugation detail
/learn/essentials    Building blocks (numbers, colours, time, position, frequency)
/reference           Reference landing page (section cards)
/reference/*         Grammar reference by topic (8 tabs)
/search              Vocabulary search
/progress            Analytics (streak calendar, accuracy trends)
/support             About page
```

## Routes

<route path="/">
<purpose>Dashboard - primary entry point and engagement hub</purpose>
<file>src/routes/home.tsx</file>
<data-source>DB: vocabularySkills (via getPracticeStats query)</data-source>
<displays>
- Due item count with time estimate (~0.25 min per item)
- Weekly streak visualisation (7-day grid, Mon-Sun)
- Freeze indicator (shows available freezes, recovery status)
- Today's phrase (rotates by day of month from 5 phrases)
- Mastered/learning counts
- Quick practice CTA (contextual: first-time user, all caught up, lapsed user, or due items)
- "Just 5 items" option when queue > 15 items
- Tomorrow preview ("X items due tomorrow")
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Tap "Start Practice" → /practice (general practice)
- Tap "Learn new items" → /practice/vocabulary (when caught up)
- Navigate via bottom nav
</user-actions>
<engagement>Primary habit trigger - due count creates urgency, streak creates loss aversion</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/login">
<purpose>User authentication - password or passkey</purpose>
<file>src/routes/login.tsx</file>
<displays>
- Username input field
- Password input field
- "Sign in" button (password auth)
- "Sign in with passkey" button (WebAuthn)
- Link to /register
- Info box for existing users to set up password
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Enter username + password → submit → logged in
- Enter username/code without password → prompted to set password (existing users)
- Click passkey button → browser WebAuthn prompt → logged in
</user-actions>
</route>

<route path="/register">
<purpose>New user account creation</purpose>
<file>src/routes/register.tsx</file>
<displays>
- Username input
- Display name input
- Password + confirmation inputs
- Optional passkey setup after registration
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Fill registration form → submit → account created
- Optionally set up passkey for future logins
- Redirected to home
</user-actions>
</route>

<route path="/try">
<purpose>Anonymous drill for try-before-signup conversion</purpose>
<file>src/routes/try.tsx</file>
<data-source>Static: 8 hardcoded pronoun questions</data-source>
<displays>
- Intro screen explaining the drill format
- Timed drill (8 questions, 4s each)
- Completion screen with stats and signup prompt
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Click "Start" to begin drill
- Type Greek answers under time pressure
- View results at completion
- Click "Create Account" → /register (to save progress)
- Click "Try Again" to repeat drill
</user-actions>
<engagement>Foot-in-the-door - experience value before commitment</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/practice">
<purpose>Redirects to /practice/speed</purpose>
<file>src/routes/practice/index.tsx</file>
<behaviour>Loader redirects to /practice/speed</behaviour>
</route>

<route path="/practice/speed">
<purpose>Timed mixed production drills - core retrieval practice</purpose>
<file>src/routes/practice/speed-drill.tsx</file>
<data-source>Static question sets + runtime-generated case transformations</data-source>
<displays>
- Countdown timer (3.5-5s per question type)
- English prompt (or Greek→case transformation prompt)
- Greek input field
- Session progress (X/Y)
- Configurable session size (10/15/20/30 questions)
</displays>
<filter-ui>
In-page filter buttons before starting drill:
- All (default) - Mixed questions from all categories
- Pronouns - Object and possessive pronouns only
- Articles - Article + noun agreement only
- Verbs - Verb conjugations only
- Nouns - Case transformation questions (ο φίλος → accusative)
</filter-ui>
<user-actions>
- Type Greek answer
- Submit (Enter or timeout)
- View feedback (correct/incorrect)
- Auto-advance to next question
- Complete session → view stats
</user-actions>
<question-types>
- Object pronouns (με, σε, τον...)
- Possessive pronouns (μου, σου...)
- Verb conjugations (έχω, θέλω, μπορώ, είμαι)
- Article + noun phrases
- Case transformations (nominative → accusative/genitive)
- Common sentences
</question-types>
<engagement>Time pressure creates flow state, variable content prevents boredom</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/practice/memory">
<purpose>Memory drill hub - timed paradigm recall for forms that need to become automatic</purpose>
<file>src/routes/practice/memory/index.tsx</file>
<data-source>Static: hardcoded paradigm data</data-source>
<displays>
- Header: "Memory Drills" with subtitle
- Paradigm cards (4 items):
  - Definite Articles (18 forms)
  - Object Pronouns (10 forms)
  - Possessive Pronouns (8 forms)
  - Contractions/σε (6 forms)
- Each card shows form count and Greek preview
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Tap a paradigm card → individual memory drill
</user-actions>
<engagement>Form count creates concrete goal, Greek preview primes recall</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/practice/memory/:drill" drills="articles,pronouns,possessives,contractions">
<purpose>Individual timed memory drills for specific paradigms</purpose>
<files>
- src/routes/practice/memory/articles.tsx
- src/routes/practice/memory/pronouns.tsx
- src/routes/practice/memory/possessives.tsx
- src/routes/practice/memory/contractions.tsx
</files>
<data-source>Static: hardcoded paradigm questions per drill type</data-source>
<displays>
- Timed recall drill for specific paradigm
- Progress indicator
- Feedback on each answer
- Session summary with accuracy
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Type Greek form under time pressure
- View feedback
- Complete drill → view stats
</user-actions>
<engagement>Focused paradigm drilling builds automaticity for specific form sets</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/practice/review">
<purpose>SRS review queue - spaced repetition for long-term retention</purpose>
<file>src/routes/practice/$tab.tsx (tab=review)</file>
<data-source>DB: vocabulary, vocabularySkills (filtered by nextReviewAt)</data-source>
<displays>
- Due item count
- Current vocabulary item
- Greek input field
- Feedback with correct answer
- Queue progress
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Type Greek translation
- Submit answer
- View feedback
- Continue to next item
- Complete queue → "All caught up!"
</user-actions>
<srs-algorithm>
- Quality 5: Correct in <2s → increase interval (easy)
- Quality 4: Correct in >=2s → increase interval (good)
- Quality 2: Incorrect → decrease interval (hard)
- Mastery threshold: 21+ day interval
</srs-algorithm>
<engagement>Due count urgency, completion satisfaction</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/practice/:tab" tabs="vocabulary,review">
<purpose>Tab container for SRS-based drills</purpose>
<file>src/routes/practice/$tab.tsx</file>
<data-source>DB: vocabulary, vocabularySkills</data-source>
<tabs>
- vocabulary: New vocabulary learning (DB, requires user)
- review: SRS review queue (DB, requires user)
</tabs>
<legacy-redirects>
- /practice/pronouns → /practice/speed
- /practice/articles → /practice/speed
- /practice/verbs → /practice/speed
- /practice/nouns → /practice/speed
</legacy-redirects>
<engagement>Focused practice on weak areas</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/learn">
<purpose>Learn section hub - visual overview of content areas</purpose>
<file>src/routes/learn/index.tsx</file>
<displays>
- Header: "Learn" with subtitle "Browse Greek content by topic"
- Two groups with section cards:
  - Communication: Conversations, Phrases
  - Words: Nouns, Verbs, Essentials
- Colour-coded borders by section (olive, ocean, honey, terracotta)
</displays>
<engagement>Progressive disclosure - browse overview, then dive into content</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/learn/conversations/:tab">
<purpose>Themed dialogues for contextual learning</purpose>
<file>src/routes/learn/conversations/$tab.tsx</file>
<data-source>Static: hardcoded dialogue content</data-source>
<tabs>
- arriving: Arriving and leaving scenarios
- food: Food and hospitality
- smalltalk: Small talk and greetings
- requests: Quick requests
</tabs>
<displays>
- Dialogue exchanges (speaker roles: you, friend, host, waiter, etc.)
- Greek text with English translation
- Study / Speak mode toggle (shared across conversations)
- Optional notes for phrases (literal meanings, context)
</displays>
<legacy-redirect>/explore/conversations/* → /learn/conversations/*</legacy-redirect>
<engagement>Real-world context, practical application</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/learn/phrases/:tab">
<purpose>Common expressions organised by function</purpose>
<file>src/routes/learn/phrases/$tab.tsx</file>
<data-source>Static: hardcoded phrase content</data-source>
<tabs>
- survival: Essential survival phrases
- responses: Response patterns
- requests: Request phrases
- opinions: Expressing opinions
- connectors: Discourse connectors
- time: Time expressions
</tabs>
<note>Grammar patterns (μου αρέσει, με λένε) moved to /reference/patterns</note>
<displays>
- Phrase cards with Greek/English
- Usage notes
- Related phrases
</displays>
<legacy-redirect>/explore/phrases/* → /learn/phrases/*</legacy-redirect>
<engagement>Quick reference, practical utility</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/learn/nouns">
<purpose>Noun browser by gender and semantic category</purpose>
<file>src/routes/learn/nouns/route.tsx</file>
<data-source>DB: vocabulary (grouped by tags)</data-source>
<displays>
- Nouns by semantic category (people, shopping, household, vehicles, summer)
- Greek text, English translation
- Gender badges
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Browse categories
</user-actions>
<engagement>Discovery mode, fill knowledge gaps</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/learn/verbs">
<purpose>Verb browser by conjugation family</purpose>
<file>src/routes/learn/verbs/route.tsx</file>
<data-source>DB: vocabulary + verbDetails</data-source>
<displays>
- Verbs by conjugation family (-ω, -άω, -μαι, irregular) with paradigm tables
- Conjugation family badges
- Collapsible sections for verb lists
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Browse families
- Expand/collapse verb lists
- Tap verb → detail page
</user-actions>
<engagement>Discovery mode, understand verb patterns</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/learn/verbs/:verbId">
<purpose>Full verb conjugation detail page</purpose>
<file>src/routes/learn/verbs/$verbId/route.tsx</file>
<data-source>DB: vocabulary, verbDetails, verbConjugations, verbImperatives</data-source>
<displays>
- Verb header (lemma, English, conjugation family badge)
- Suppletive indicator (if different stems across tenses)
- Stem insight (present/aorist/future stem changes)
- Tense navigator (tabs: present, aorist, future, past continuous)
- Paradigm tables (6 forms: sg1-3, pl1-3)
- Imperative table (imperfective/perfective × singular/plural)
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Switch between tenses
- Study stem changes
- Back to verb list
</user-actions>
<engagement>Deep study mode, understand verb patterns</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/reference">
<purpose>Reference section hub - visual overview of grammar topics</purpose>
<file>src/routes/reference/index.tsx</file>
<displays>
- Header: "Reference" with subtitle "Grammar patterns and paradigms"
- Section cards with icons linking to each of 8 tabs
- Colour-coded borders by topic (ocean, olive, honey, terracotta)
</displays>
<engagement>Progressive disclosure - browse overview, then dive into specifics</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/reference/:tab">
<purpose>Grammar reference lookup</purpose>
<file>src/routes/reference/$tab.tsx</file>
<data-source>Static: hardcoded grammar content + DB for patterns</data-source>
<tabs>
- cases: Case system foundation (nominative, accusative, genitive)
- pronouns: Pronoun paradigms, decision guides, indefinite reference
- articles: Article paradigms, gender agreement, movable nu
- nouns: Noun declensions by gender (masculine, feminine, neuter)
- adjectives: Adjective agreement patterns
- prepositions: Preposition + case combinations
- verbs: Conjugation patterns, tense overview
- patterns: Greek-specific constructions (μου αρέσει, με λένε)
</tabs>
<note>8 tabs total. Articles tab component is nouns-articles.tsx (combines article paradigms with noun gender context).</note>
<displays>
- Tab navigation bar
- Paradigm tables
- Decision guides (flowcharts)
- Usage examples
- Pattern explanations
</displays>
<engagement>Just-in-time reference when stuck</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/search">
<purpose>Fuzzy vocabulary search</purpose>
<file>src/routes/search.tsx</file>
<data-source>DB: vocabulary (via @mmmike/mikrofuzz)</data-source>
<displays>
- Search input (autofocus)
- Results list with Greek, English, word type, tags
- Fuzzy matching (tolerates typos, ranked by relevance)
- Color-coded left borders by word type (verb=ocean, noun=olive, phrase=terracotta, adverb=honey)
</displays>
<user-actions>
- Type query (Greek, English, or tag name)
- View matching results inline
- Clear search to reset
</user-actions>
<engagement>Quick lookup utility</engagement>
<target-ux>
**Mobile:** Bottom drawer that slides up from nav tap
- Search input at top of drawer
- Results below, scrollable
- Swipe down or tap outside to dismiss

**Desktop:** Autocomplete dropdown from nav
- Click "Search" in nav → popover appears below
- Type to filter results inline
- Click result or press Escape to dismiss

**Future enhancement:** Selecting a word shows forms (conjugations, declensions)
</target-ux>
</route>

<route path="/progress">
<purpose>Analytics and progress tracking</purpose>
<file>src/routes/progress.tsx</file>
<data-source>DB: practiceSessions, practiceAttempts, vocabularySkills</data-source>
<displays>
- Streak calendar (3-month view, practice days highlighted)
- Accuracy trend chart (30-day rolling)
- Time invested (total minutes, session count)
- Mastered vocabulary count
</displays>
<user-actions>
- View historical practice data
- Navigate back to dashboard
</user-actions>
<engagement>Investment visibility, progress reinforcement</engagement>
</route>

<route path="/support">
<purpose>About page - project story and support options</purpose>
<file>src/routes/support.tsx</file>
<displays>
- Project backstory (why this app exists)
- Creator context (learning Greek for family)
- Support options (Buy Me a Coffee link)
</displays>
<engagement>Trust building, personal connection</engagement>
</route>

## Core Engagement Loop

```
Open app → Dashboard ("X due") → Practice (2-3 min) → Streak updated → Close
```

## Engagement Hooks

<hooks>
<hook name="due-count" location="dashboard" mechanism="urgency">
Shows number of items due for review, creates FOMO
</hook>
<hook name="streak-display" location="dashboard" mechanism="loss-aversion">
Weekly grid showing practice days, users don't want to break chain
</hook>
<hook name="short-sessions" location="practice" mechanism="low-friction">
2-3 minute sessions, easy to fit into spare moments
</hook>
<hook name="auto-advance" location="speed-drill" mechanism="flow-state">
Correct answers auto-advance, maintains momentum
</hook>
<hook name="push-notifications" location="system" mechanism="external-prompt">
Remind users to practice, preserve streaks
</hook>
<hook name="lapsed-user-recovery" location="dashboard" mechanism="reduced-friction">
Users returning after 7+ days with 15+ due items see contextual "Welcome back" messaging with "Just 5 items" option
</hook>
<hook name="post-session-celebration" location="drill-summary" mechanism="positive-reinforcement">
Variable encouragement messages with icons based on accuracy (Trophy/Flame/Sparkles)
</hook>
<hook name="milestone-celebration" location="dashboard" mechanism="achievement">
Confetti + modal at 7, 30, 100, 365 day streaks - persisted so only shown once
</hook>
<hook name="streak-warning-notification" location="system" mechanism="loss-aversion">
Push notification at 8pm UTC for users at risk of losing streak
</hook>
</hooks>

## Current Gaps

<gaps>
<gap name="streak-reset" status="implemented">
<current>Streak freeze system with auto-activation</current>
<details>
- Earn 1 freeze per 7 consecutive days (max 3)
- Auto-activates on missed day
- 24h cooldown between freeze uses
- Dashboard shows freeze count and status
</details>
</gap>
<gap name="streak-warning" status="implemented">
<current>Push notification at 8pm UTC for users who haven't practiced</current>
<details>
- Cron trigger in wrangler.toml (0 20 * * *)
- Checks users with active streaks who haven't practiced today
- Sends "Don't lose your X-day streak!" notification
</details>
</gap>
<gap name="milestones" status="implemented">
<current>Celebration modal at 7, 30, 100, 365 days</current>
<details>
- MilestoneCelebration component shows confetti + message
- Persisted to milestonesAchieved table via /api/milestones
- Only shows once per milestone per user
</details>
</gap>
<gap name="tomorrow-hook" status="implemented">
<current>Dashboard shows "Tomorrow: X items" with calendar icon</current>
</gap>
</gaps>

## Data Tables

<tables>
<table name="users">User accounts (id, code, username, displayName, passwordHash, freezeCount, lastFreezeUsedAt, freezeUsedForDate, consecutiveDaysAtEarn)</table>
<table name="passkeys">WebAuthn credentials (userId, credentialId, publicKey, counter, transports, deviceType, backedUp, lastUsedAt)</table>
<table name="authChallenges">WebAuthn challenge storage (challenge, type, userId, expiresAt) - 5min TTL</table>
<table name="vocabulary">All Greek words/phrases (greekText, englishTranslation, wordType, gender, metadata, declensionPattern)</table>
<table name="tags">Vocabulary categorisation (slug, name, description)</table>
<table name="tagSections">UI display organisation (tagId, section, displayOrder)</table>
<table name="vocabularyTags">Many-to-many vocab↔tag join table</table>
<table name="verbDetails">Verb metadata (conjugationFamily, stems, isSuppletive, notes)</table>
<table name="verbConjugations">Full verb paradigms by tense (vocabId, tense, person, form)</table>
<table name="verbImperatives">Imperative forms (vocabId, aspect, number, form)</table>
<table name="practiceSessions">Session metadata (userId, sessionType, category, timestamps)</table>
<table name="practiceAttempts">Practice history (sessionId, vocabId, isCorrect, timeTaken)</table>
<table name="weakAreas">Pattern-based weak spots (userId, areaType, identifier, errorCount)</table>
<table name="vocabularySkills">SRS state per user per word (easeFactor, intervalDays, reviewCount, nextReviewAt)</table>
<table name="pushSubscriptions">Push notification endpoints (userId, endpoint, keys)</table>
<table name="milestonesAchieved">Milestone celebrations shown (userId, milestoneType, achievedAt)</table>
</tables>

## User State

- Session in localStorage (`greek-authenticated-user`) as JSON: `{userId, username}`
- Authentication via username/password or WebAuthn passkey
- Existing users without passwords prompted to set one on first login
- Registration creates new account with password, optional passkey setup

## Navigation Architecture

### Current State

**Mobile:**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  [Ellinika]                   [🔍] [👤] │  ← Header: logo, search, profile
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                         │
│            [Page Content]               │
│                                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  [Home] [Practice] [Learn] [Reference]  │  ← Bottom nav: 4 items
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Desktop (header):**
```
[Ellinika]     [Practice] [Learn] [Reference] [🔍 Search] [Account ▾]
```

### Mobile Navigation (Implemented)

**Mobile header (top bar):**
```
[Ellinika]                    [🔍] [👤]
```
- Logo → Home
- Search icon → opens search drawer
- Profile icon → opens account drawer (Progress, About, Sign Out)

**Mobile bottom nav (4 items):**
```
[🏠 Home] [⚡ Practice] [📖 Learn] [📋 Reference]
```

This follows the Instagram/Duolingo pattern of minimal top bar + bottom nav.

### Problem: Search is Hidden on Mobile

Search only exists in the header. On mobile:
1. User scrolls down to practice/browse
2. Header scrolls out of view
3. User wants to look up a word
4. Must scroll ALL the way back up
5. Find tiny search icon in header
6. Tap

**This is high friction for a frequently-used feature.**

### Navigation Options (Mobile-First)

#### Option A: Add Search to Bottom Nav
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  [Home] [Practice] [🔍] [Learn] [Ref]   │  ← 5 items
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```
- **Pro:** Always accessible, one tap
- **Pro:** Follows mobile convention (Instagram, Spotify)
- **Con:** 5 items is crowded but acceptable
- **Con:** Search competes with Practice for attention

#### Option B: Floating Action Button (FAB)
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                    [🔍] │  ← Floating button
│            [Page Content]               │
│                                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  [Home] [Practice] [Learn] [Reference]  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```
- **Pro:** Always visible, doesn't take nav space
- **Pro:** Can animate/hide during drills
- **Con:** Covers content, can feel intrusive
- **Con:** Non-standard for search

#### Option C: Search in Header (Sticky)
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  [Ellinika]                       [🔍]  │  ← Sticky mini-header
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│            [Page Content]               │
│                                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  [Home] [Practice] [Learn] [Reference]  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```
- **Pro:** Search always visible
- **Pro:** Preserves bottom nav simplicity
- **Con:** Takes vertical space (precious on mobile)
- **Con:** Two navigation areas to manage

#### Option D: Replace "Home" with Search
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  [🔍] [Practice] [Learn] [Reference]    │  ← Search replaces Home
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```
- **Pro:** No new nav item, cleaner
- **Pro:** Practice IS home for learners (analyst feedback)
- **Pro:** Logo tap → home (standard pattern)
- **Con:** Losing explicit "Home" might confuse some users

#### Option E: Long-press/Swipe Gesture
```
Long-press Practice → Search overlay
Swipe down anywhere → Search overlay
```
- **Pro:** No UI changes needed
- **Con:** Completely hidden, zero discoverability
- **Con:** Gesture conflicts possible

### Recommendation: Option D (Replace Home with Search)

**Rationale:**
1. **Mobile-first:** Keeps 4-item bottom nav (optimal thumb reach)
2. **Practice-centric:** Practice IS the primary destination (curriculum analyst feedback)
3. **Standard pattern:** Logo → Home is universal (users expect it)
4. **Search accessible:** One tap from anywhere
5. **Clean:** No floating buttons or extra nav bars

**Current mobile nav (implemented):**
```
Top bar:    [Ellinika]              [🔍] [👤]
Bottom nav: [🏠 Home] [⚡ Practice] [📖 Learn] [📋 Reference]
```

- Search icon in header opens search drawer
- Profile icon in header opens account drawer (authenticated only)
- Unauthenticated users see "Sign In" link instead of profile icon

**During active drills:** Consider hiding search to prevent "cheating" (separate feature)

### Desktop Navigation

Desktop has more space. Proposed structure:

**Authenticated:**
```
[Ellinika]                    [Practice ←CTA] [Learn] [Reference] [Search] [User ▾]
                                                                            └── Progress
                                                                                Settings
                                                                                About
                                                                                ────────
                                                                                Sign Out
```

**Unauthenticated:**
```
[Ellinika]                    [Learn] [Reference] [Search] [Sign In] [Try a Drill ←CTA]
```

### Routes by Nav Location

| Route | Mobile | Desktop | Notes |
|-------|--------|---------|-------|
| `/` | Home (bottom nav) | Logo tap | Dashboard/home |
| `/practice/speed` | Practice (bottom nav) | Practice (CTA) | Primary action |
| `/learn` | Learn (bottom nav) | Learn | Landing page → subsections |
| `/reference` | Reference (bottom nav) | Reference | Landing page → tabs |
| `/search` | Search icon (header) | Search | Vocabulary search |
| `/progress` | Profile drawer | User menu | Analytics (authenticated) |
| `/support` | Profile drawer | User menu | About page |
| `/try` | — | Try a Drill (unauth) | Conversion CTA |
| `/login` | Sign In (header) | Sign In (unauth) | Auth |
| `/register` | — | Via /try flow | Account creation |
